%N A318958 A(n, k) is a square array read in the decreasing antidiagonals, for n >= 0 and k >= 0.
%F A318958 Let h(n) = 0, 0, -1, A198442(1), A198442(2), A198442(3), ... Then A(n, 0) = h(n), A(n, 1) = h(n+1) and A(n, k) = A(n, k-2) + n otherwise.
